{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01H7pZz4VyVZZuFvKbsQX3id","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the knowledge file against the source file carefully.\n\n**Source file content:**\nThe source is a FAQ about how to easily perform condition coverage testing for SQL statements executed within Action classes.\n\n**Question (problem description):**\n- When performing condition coverage tests for SQL in Action classes using request unit tests, test effort increases\n- To test a single SQL, you need to prepare all other SQL information used in that request\n- Confirming SQL execution results is difficult because you can only check request output\n- Hard to verify if data was truly absent or just happened to match due to other SQL/components\n- All data must be confirmed, increasing review effort\n\n**Answer:**\n1. Not all test cases need to be implemented as request unit tests - use class unit tests as needed\n\n\n2. The complexity of SQL and business logic condition coverage grows rapidly as input combinations increase, making request unit tests inefficient due to the extensive data setup required for each test case.\n3. By extracting the logic into a separate component class, you can test it directly with class unit tests, allowing you to control input variables and referenced table contents without the overhead of request-level setup.\n4. This approach significantly reduces both the effort needed to create tests and the effort required to review them.\n5. For more details, see the programming unit test guide section on class unit test implementation methods for Action and Component classes. 見つけるべき情報は、クラス単体テストの実装方法についての詳細なガイドとサンプルコードがどこにあるかを示す参照先だ。つまり、Action/Componentのクラス単体テストに関する具体的な実装例を別のセクションで確認できるということだね。 I'm recognizing that this reference to another document is just a navigation pointer, which falls under acceptable omissions according to the rules. But the question secti